# Railway Environment Variables - Quick Reference

## Required for Railway Deployment

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://user:password@host:5432/dbname
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-min-32-chars
```

## Optional (Recommended)

```
API_BASE_URL=https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app
CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend.vercel.app
```

## How to Set in Railway Dashboard

1. Go to **Variables** section
2. Click **Add Variable** button
3. Enter each key-value pair:

### Example for Railway:
```
Key: DATABASE_URL
Value: (Copy from Railway PostgreSQL service)

Key: SECRET_KEY
Value: (Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32)

Key: API_BASE_URL
Value: https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app

Key: CORS_ORIGINS
Value: https://your-frontend.vercel.app
```

## What's Changed

✅ `api_base_url` is now **optional** (not required)
✅ Smart fallback: CORS_ORIGINS → API_BASE_URL → localhost default
✅ Application won't crash if API_BASE_URL is missing
✅ Compatible with Pydantic v2 and pydantic-settings

## Local Testing

```bash
cd backend
python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# Should start without validation errors
```

## Deploy to Railway

```bash
git add app/config.py .env
git commit -m "Fix: Make API_BASE_URL optional with CORS fallbacks for Railway"
git push origin main
```

Railway will automatically redeploy. Check the logs to verify no validation errors! 🚀
